    longDescription: 'In December 1993, Senators Joseph Lieberman and Herb Kohl convened hearings to examine whether violent and sexually explicit video games posed a threat to children. Mortal Kombat\'s digitised gore — particularly its fatality moves — and Night Trap\'s live-action footage of women in lingerie being attacked by vampires were held up as exhibits of industry irresponsibility. The industry was given a six-month ultimatum: establish a voluntary ratings system or face federal regulation. The hearings were nationally televised and generated enormous press coverage, transforming the public perception of games from a children\'s toy into a contested cultural medium.',
